The much-anticipated Form One selection that was scheduled to be launched tomorrow has been pushed to Tuesday next week.&quot;This is to invite you to the launch of the 2017 Form One selection that will take place at the Kenya Institute of Curriculum Development (KICD) on Tuesday December 13,&quot; a statement by Education PS Belio Kipsang&#39; Wednesday &nbsp;read. Education Cabinet Secretary Fred Matiang&#39;i will preside over the ceremony. However, the reporting date for Form One students remains January 9.The circular was sent to all regional education coordinators and county directors of education.Dr Matiang&#39;i said the 5,143 pupils who scored 400 marks and above will get places in the 103 national schools. ALSO READ: Secrets of new system as 8-4-4 to end